. * --- feTR ---
. di _n "=== feTR: oda ~ i_elecex ==="

=== feTR: oda ~ i_elecex ===

. cap scalar drop nplus nminus beta sumpositive sumnegative

. cap noisily twowayfeweights oda pair_id year i_elecex, type(feTR) summary_mea
> sures

Under the common trends assumption,
the TWFE coefficient beta, equal to 2.1827, estimates a weighted sum of 1370 AT
> Ts. 
1370 ATTs receive a positive weight, and 0 receive a negative weight.
------------------------------------------------
Treat. var: i_elecex    # ATTs      Σ weights  
------------------------------------------------
Positive weights        1370        1.0000      
Negative weights        0           0.0000      
------------------------------------------------
Total                   1370        1.0000      
------------------------------------------------

Summary Measures:
TWFE coefficient (β_fe) =    2.1827
min σ(Δ) compatible with β_fe and Δ_TR = 0:   31.7941
Reference: Corollary 1, de Chaisemartin, C and D'Haultfoeuille, X (2020a)


